{
  "stem": "4361.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now to be-- in her younger years before she married my grandfather, whom I never knew.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But in those days-- I'm speaking about early 20th century or late 19th century.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "First of all, for a woman to be a schoolteacher was extraordinary.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And for a Jewish woman to be a schoolteacher, it was doubly extraordinary.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But she was, and I remember my grandmother Miriam teaching me the names of flowers as a little girl, teaching me how to count.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I, I, I remember her with such warmth and such reverence, and she died.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, because although, as I understand and from what I've read and learned, there was no overt anti-Semitism in Austro-Hungary.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was sub rosa.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was always underneath.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so certain things, Jews did not do because, first of all, they knew ahead of time that they could not succeed.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And secondly, particularly in my grandmother's case, I would imagine that for a Jewish family in those days-- and they were very religious, as I understood, orthodox-- to allow their daughter to go out and teach was in and of itself something very special.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And in a way, that was almost translated many, many years later when I told my parents as a teenager, 14 or 15, that I want to go and study law.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was, you know, doing something against the accepted norm.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "A girl, at best, will have her baccalaureate.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Even that was already quite an achievement.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And after that, she's getting married.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Meanwhile, she would learn to play the piano, speak a little French.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But to go to law school, who ever heard of that?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But I did feel that I, I did-- I would have liked to.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
